      "source": [
        "# Airbnb Hotel Booking Analysis – CSV Version\n",
        "# -------------------------------------------\n",
        "\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import seaborn as sns\n",
        "import os\n",
        "\n",
        "# File path (make sure the name matches the file visible in the left panel)\n",
        "DATA_PATH = '/content/1730285881-Airbnb_Open_Data.csv'\n",
        "\n",
        "# Load the dataset\n",
        "df = pd.read_csv(DATA_PATH, encoding='utf-8')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Basic info about the dataset\n",
        "print(\" Dataset loaded successfully!\")\n",
        "print(\"Shape (Rows, Columns):\", df.shape)\n",
        "print(\"\\nColumn Names:\\n\", df.columns.tolist())\n",
        "\n",
        "# Display first 5 rows\n",
        "df.head()\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Data Cleaning and Preprocessing\n",
        "\n",
        "# Remove dollar signs and convert price & service fee to numeric\n",
        "df['price'] = df['price'].replace(r'[\\$,]', '', regex=True).astype(float)\n",
        "df['service fee'] = df['service fee'].replace(r'[\\$,]', '', regex=True).astype(float)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Handle missing values\n",
        "df.fillna({\n",
        "    'reviews per month': 0,\n",
        "    'review rate number': df['review rate number'].median()\n",
        "}, inplace=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Verify cleaned data\n",
        "df.info()\n"
      ],
